      "message": "I\u0027d recommend not supporting manually set statuses.\n\nSupporting this allows two ways of doing the same thing that will likely lead to harder to understand client code.\n\nClients will have to make the decision whether or not to return an error, based on whether or not something deeper in their logic has already set the status, or might be surprised when a returned error has no effect on the status.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 103,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 103,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "6c25df5c385468967569dce9e4a0be2c04979e30",
