    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c0ccbc26_9aee652a",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/step.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 114,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-14T17:20:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s not an antipattern, but \u0027steps\u0027 here in Go land are strictly about updating the Build. I expect to see things like:\n\n   func QueryDatastore(ctx, ...) (dat *Data, err error) {\n     err \u003d exe.WithStep(..., func(ctx, s *Step) (err error) {\n        dat, err \u003d doQuery()\n        return\n     })\n     return \n   }\n\nWhere user code would call QueryDatastore to get their two values.\n\nIt\u0027s a bit messy, but I think this is clearer than some sort of information passing scheme.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "469a92f1_50553b96",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 114,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 114,
        "endChar": 13
      },
